.SH NAME
MediaQueryListEvent.matches \- MediaQueryListEvent: matches property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]matches\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]MediaQueryListEvent\f[R] interface is a boolean value that is
\f[CR]true\f[R] if the \f[CR]document\f[R] currently matches the media
query list, or \f[CR]false\f[R] if not.
.SH VALUE
A boolean value; returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if the \f[CR]document\f[R]
currently matches the media query list, \f[CR]false\f[R] if not.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
const para = document.querySelector(\[dq]p\[dq]); // This is the UI element where to display the text
const mql = window.matchMedia(\[dq](max\-width: 600px)\[dq]);

mql.addEventListener(\[dq]change\[dq], (event) => {
  if (event.matches) {
    // The viewport is 600 pixels wide or less
    para.textContent = \[dq]This is a narrow screen \[em] less than 600px wide.\[dq];
    document.body.style.backgroundColor = \[dq]red\[dq];
  } else {
    // The viewport is more than 600 pixels wide
    para.textContent = \[dq]This is a wide screen \[em] more than 600px wide.\[dq];
    document.body.style.backgroundColor = \[dq]blue\[dq];
  }
});
